          "date": "2014-02-24 20:12:00.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-4495 ldlm: distributed deadlock with clio.",
        "message": "LU-4495 ldlm: distributed deadlock with clio.\n\nEarly sublock allocation enter to situation with practically cached\nlocks. In that case we may hit deadlock when client1 linked a sub1,\nsub2 as new sublocks, but sub3 as cached sublock, so client2 will hold\nsub1,sub2 and tries to enqueue a sub3.. so it's deadlock as releasing\na sub3 blocked by enqueue a sub1.\n\nXyratex-bug-id: CLSTR-2003\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell<paf@cray.com>\nSigned-off-by: Alexey Lyashkov <alexey_lyashkov@xyratex.com>\nChange-Id: I8c792081b415464451b014584e7188a47757f955\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
